  "prompt": "If I connect USB OTG pendrive to my power bank and connect the other point with data cable to my mobile, will pendrive be working on my mobile?",
  "response": "Connecting a USB OTG (On-The-Go) pendrive to your mobile device typically requires that the pendrive be directly connected to the mobile device through an OTG adapter or an OTG cable. Here\u2019s a simplified explanation of how this works:\n\n1. **OTG Adapter/Cable**: You need an OTG adapter or cable to connect the USB pendrive to your mobile device. The OTG adapter/cable has a micro USB or USB-C connector on one end (to connect to your phone) and a USB-A port on the other end (to connect the pendrive).\n\n2. **Direct Connection**: The pendrive should be directly connected to the mobile device via the OTG adapter/cable. This direct connection allows the mobile device to recognize and interface with the pendrive.\n\n3. **Power Bank Connection**: If you connect the pendrive to a power bank, it would only provide power but not facilitate data transfer. The power bank\u2019s USB ports are typically not designed to host USB devices for data transfer. They can only charge devices or provide power.\n\nTherefore, for the pendrive to work on your mobile device, you should avoid connecting it to the power bank for data transfer purposes. Instead, use an OTG adapter or cable to connect the pendrive directly to your mobile device.",
